# Infinite Vision — Project & Codebase

## Purpose
Official website for **Infinite Vision, Incorporated** — veteran-led, Memphis-based nonprofit integrating **Housing, Transportation, and Financial Empowerment**.

Every change must reflect: veteran-centered tone, Memphis identity, professional nonprofit UX, accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA), scalability, and deploy stability.

## Stack & structure
- **Next.js 14 App Router** (`app/`), React Server Components where appropriate
- **Components**: `app/components/` (or `components/` if added)
- **Styles**: `styles/globals.css` (project uses global CSS, not Tailwind unless migrated)
- **Assets**: `public/` (logo: `public/infinite-vision-logo.png`)
- Keep navigation simple, keyboard-accessible, mobile-responsive, SEO-friendly

## Code quality
- Modular, reusable components; consistent imports and paths
- Fix broken imports, routing, hydration, and build errors when possible
- No deprecated Next.js patterns, unnecessary dependencies, or breaking changes without asking
- Ask before deleting files or major refactors
- No lorem ipsum; no placeholders except testimonials

## Local dev & deploy readiness
- Site runs with `npm run dev`; production build with `npm run build`
- Keep Vercel-compatible (no auth/DNS changes by agent)
- Prepare clear commit messages when user requests commits; never commit unless asked
